# Table Module Rules

This is a NestJS + Vue 3 data table module. Follow these patterns.

## Creating a Table
1. TypeORM entity → 2. Table class (extends BaseTable, @TableConfig) → 3. Controller (TableQueryService.execute) → 4. Frontend (<DataTable endpoint="..." />)

## Columns
TextColumn, NumericColumn, DateColumn, DateTimeColumn, BooleanColumn, BadgeColumn, ImageColumn, ActionColumn
All support: .sortable(), .searchable(), .toggleable(), .mapAs(fn), .exportAs(fn)
ActionColumn.make() always goes last.

## Filters
TextFilter (ILIKE), NumericFilter (comparisons), DateFilter (date comparisons), BooleanFilter (IsTrue/IsFalse), SetFilter (.options([])), TrashedFilter (auto-added with softDeletes)
All support: .clauses([]), .nullable(), .default(val), .applyUsing(fn)

## Actions
Action.make('name').asButton().variant(Variant.Destructive).confirm({title}).handle(async (item, repo) => ...)
Action.make('name').asLink().url((row) => `/path/${row.id}`)
Action.make('name').bulk() for multi-select actions

## Exports
Export.make('Name', 'file.xlsx', ExportFormat.Xlsx) — runs async with SSE progress

